data.title: Zoomlion celebrates World Cities Day 2025 by backing urban development, with focus on smart cities.
data.description: In Changsha, China, Zoomlion Heavy Industry Science & Technology Co., Ltd. (stock symbol: 1157.HK) is commemorating World Cities Day 2025 by reaffirming its commitment to sustainable urban development, interconnected transportation, and the advancement of smart cities.

data.title: China leads in urban health-climate solutions with 8 of 13 indicators at record highs; paves way for global south.
data.description: The recently released Lancet Countdown China report indicates that 8 out of 13 climate-health risk indicators have reached their highest levels in history. The launch event in Beijing on October 31, 2025, highlighted scalable strategies for fostering resilient and low-carbon urban development. This report underscores the urgency of addressing these challenges, with numbers like eight out of thirteen indicators peaking, signaling the need for immediate action to combat climate-related health risks.

data.title: FastGPT is recognized as a top no-code, open-source AI Agent Builder for 2025, enabling enterprises to build intelligent workflows.
data.description: In Singapore on October 31, 2025, the growing trend of incorporating artificial intelligence in businesses is evident. Companies are looking to adopt AI-driven automation and intelligence in their operations. FastGPT, an Enterprise-class AI Agent Builder, is playing a key role in this transformation, providing advanced solutions without compromising on quality. This signifies the ongoing shift towards utilizing AI technologies in various sectors to enhance efficiency and performance.

data.title: McKay Brothers gets minority investments from Optiver and Qube, announced on Oct. 31, 2025, for its financial data services.
data.description: In a recent press release date October 31, 2025, McKay Brothers, a prominent company based in Oakland, California, Chicago, Geneva, and Paris, shared that they have partnered with Optiver and Qube Research & Technologies (QRT). McKay Brothers, known for its expertise in sourcing and delivering financial data quickly and reliably between financial institutions, will be working alongside these entities to enhance their services further. The collaboration with Optiver and Qube Research & Technologies holds great promise, potentially impacting the financial industry with their combined resources.

data.title: Mycenax Biotech signs agreement with RIN Institute to use VLK linker technology in CDMO, based in Taiwan | Oct. 31, 2025.
data.description: On October 31, 2025, a prominent biologics Contract Development and Manufacturing Organization (CDMO) named Mycenax Biotech Inc. from Taiwan (TWO:4726) revealed an official License Agreement with RIN Institute Inc. in Japan. This grants Mycenax the authorization to utilize RIN's distinctive Val-Leu-Lys (VLK) linker technology within their CDMO services.

data.title: Tetragon Financial Group's Sep 2025 factsheet shows $3.88 billion in Net Asset Value, $42.19 Fully Diluted NAV per Share, and 7.1% Total Return.
data.description: At the end of September 2025, Tetragon unveiled its Monthly Factsheet, revealing key financial figures. data.title: Kalmar's Q3 2025 report shows record-high operating profit margin of 13.8%, with orders received at EUR 375 million, down 10%. Sales increased 3% to EUR 436 million, while profit for the period was EUR 45 million. Cash flow from operations was EUR 26 million. Orders for the period totaled EUR 1,306 million, an increase of 9%, with an order book of EUR 961 million. Operating profit in the period was EUR 160 million. Kalmar expects a comparable operating profit margin above 12% in 2025. The company emphasizes sustainability and innovation in its strategy for growth. Kalmar's vision includes targets for sales growth, comparable operating profit margin, ROCE, leverage, dividend payout ratio, and a commitment to the SBTi targets. The full article is available on Benzinga.com.
data.description: Kalmar Corporation released its interim report for January-September 2025, on October 31, 2025. The report highlights an improved profitability with a record-high comparable operating profit margin of 13.8%. Equipment orders received declined by 20% compared to the previous period, but year-to-date showed solid growth. In July-September 2025, orders received totaled EUR 375 million, down by 10%, while the order book stood at EUR 961 million. Sales increased by 3% to EUR 436 million. Operating profit was EUR 61 million, representing 13.9% of sales. Cash flow from operations was EUR 26 million. Profit for the period amounted to EUR 45 million. For January-September 2025, orders received increased by 9%, reaching EUR 1,306 million. Sales decreased by 2% to EUR 1,254 million. Operating profit was EUR 160 million, representing 12.8% of sales. Cash flow from operations was EUR 133 million, and profit for the period was EUR 118 million. The company expects its comparable operating profit margin to be above 12% for the year. Kalmar achieved various sustainability milestones and financial targets for 2028 include sales growth of 5% per annum, a 15% comparable operating profit margin, and a dividend payout ratio of 30-50% annually, among others. Kalmar is committed to sustainable innovations and operational excellence to drive profitability and growth.
